From: youngjinj <youngjinj@cubrid.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix use-after-unfix in fhs_find_bucket_vpid_with_hash

`fhs_find_bucket_vpid_with_hash()` computed a pointer into the directory
page (`dir_record_p = dir_page_p + location`), then called
`pgbuf_unfix_and_init` BEFORE dereferencing the pointer to read the
bucket VPID.

After `pgbuf_unfix_and_init`, the directory page's BCB becomes a victim
candidate. Under parallel hash join (`HASH_METH_HASH_FILE` path) with
high parallelism (parallel(16)+), another worker or the flush daemon can
victimize the BCB and load a different page into the same memory between
the unfix and the dereference. The dereference then reads bytes from
whichever page now occupies that BCB, producing a garbage VPID such as
`(25401, 99)`.

The garbage VPID is then passed to `fhs_fix_old_page` -> `pgbuf_fix` ->
`pgbuf_claim_bcb_for_fix` -> `fileio_get_volume_descriptor`, which
returns `NULL_VOLDES` (-1) for the unmapped volid, and the subsequent
`pread(-1, ...)` fails with `errno=EBADF`. The user observes:

    An I/O error occurred while reading page <garbage> of volume
    "(null)".... Bad file descriptor

with a stack trace:

    fileio_read
      <- pgbuf_claim_bcb_for_fix
      <- pgbuf_fix_release
      <- fhs_fix_old_page
      <- fhs_search
      <- hjoin_probe_key
      <- hjoin_probe
      <- parallel_query::hash_join::join_task::execute

Fix: read the bucket VPID FIRST (while the directory page is still
fixed), THEN unfix the page.

Reproduced and verified against demodb t1 (50M rows) self-join with
`select /*+ parallel(16) use_hash */ count(*) from t1 a, t1 b where
a.c1 = b.c1` running in 3 concurrent csql sessions:

  before fix: hit within ~25 minutes
  after  fix: 90 minutes / 108 iterations / 0 occurrences

---
 src/query/query_hash_scan.c | 8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/query/query_hash_scan.c b/src/query/query_hash_scan.c
--- a/src/query/query_hash_scan.c
+++ b/src/query/query_hash_scan.c
@@ -1775,10 +1775,14 @@ fhs_find_bucket_vpid_with_hash (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FHSID * fhsid_p, void *
     {
       return ER_FAILED;
     }
+  /* CBRD-26666: READ the bucket VPID while the directory page is still
+   * fixed, THEN unfix. Previously the page was unfixed before the
+   * dereference, which allowed another thread (or the flush daemon) to
+   * victimize the BCB and load a different page into the same memory,
+   * causing *out_vpid_p to contain bytes from the replacement page. */
   dir_record_p = (FHS_DIR_RECORD *) ((char *) dir_page_p + location);
-  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_page_p);
-
   *out_vpid_p = dir_record_p->bucket_vpid;
+  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_page_p);

   return NO_ERROR;
 }
